    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small to medium-sized clapper bells, usually mounted in a fixture extending from the wall at the sacristy door of a Christian church, rung to announce the entrance procession of the liturgical celebrants. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
